How to Add New Tests
================================================================================
0. Move your unit testing cpp file to tests/testXYZ.cpp.  Where XYZ is the most
recent three digit number.  1. Open tests/Makefile
2. Add a new test target.  Like so:

testXYZ:
   cp testXYZ.cpp $(testdir)
   cd $(testdir) && make testXYZ

3. Open tests/Makefile.Tests
4. Add a new testXYZ target.
5. Add the g++ command line that successfully compiles the file.
6. After #4 and #5 you should have:

testXYZ:
   g++ -o testXYZ test.cpp <cpp files needed to compile>

How to Run a Test
================================================================================
0. Type: make testXYZ

How to Clean Up $(testdir)
================================================================================
0. Type: make clean
